{
  "id": "farhana-zamil-tinny-phd",
  "name": "Farhana Zamil Tinny, PhD",
  "title": "Assistant Professor",
  "department": "School of Social Science",
  "school": "",
  "profile_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/faculty/farhana-zamil-tinny-phd",
  "photo_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/sites/default/files/styles/faculty_avatar/public/images/faculty/Farhana-Zamil.jpg?itok=QxPxUI87",
  "bio_raw": "Dr. Farhana Zamil Tinny is a multidisciplinary scholar and communication professional with over a decade of experience bridging academia, qualitative research, public relations, advertising, and media production. She currently serves as an Assistant Professor at the Department of Media Studies and Journalism (MSJ), integrating industry experience and academic scholarship in her teaching.\nShe has previously taught a range of courses, including academic writing, media planning, advertising, and public speaking at Limkokwing University of Creative Technology in Malaysia. Her industry portfolio includes copywriting, media planning, and business operations for global brands, including leading international organizations and UN agencies.\nFocusing on the intersections of intercultural communication and migration, her doctoral research investigated the complex social dynamics of the Rohingya refugee crisis in Bangladesh. Grounded in their lived experiences, her research examines how displaced individuals across different age and gender groups navigate diverse adaptation strategies, negotiate their identities, and foster a sense of belonging.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Intercultural Communication, Migration and Refugee Studies, Identity and Belonging, Qualitative Research, Public Relations."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nPhD\n(Communication), Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia, Malaysia\nMCom\n(Public Relations), Limkokwing University of Creative Technology, Malaysia\nMA in English\n(ELT & Applied Linguistics), BRAC University\nBA in English\n(Media & Cultural Studies), BRAC University"
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Journal Articles\nTinny, F. Z., Ahmad, A. L., Sannusi, S. N., & Ab. Wahab, A. (2025). The Rohingya Refugees and their Acculturation Process in Bangladesh. E-Bangi Journal of Social Science and Humanities, 22(3).\nhttps://doi.org/10.17576/ebangi.2025.2203.13\nTinny, F. Z., & Ahmad, A. L. (2024). Issues and challenges in acculturation among the Rohingya refugees in Bangladesh: A systematic literature review. JURNAL KOMUNIKASI: MALAYSIAN JOURNAL OF COMMUNICATION, 40(4), 217-234.",
    "Book Chapter\nAhmed, S., & Tinny, F. Z. (2011). The RJ style: brought to you by Bangladeshi FM Radio.\nStamford Journal of English\n, 6, 1–28.",
    "Conference Proceedings\nTinny, F. Z., & Soladoye, B. A. (2019). A Qualitative Study on Scopes and Gaps in Re-Branding Bangladesh Through Effective Communication. European Journal of Multidisciplinary Studies, 4(3), 27.\nhttps://doi.org/10.26417/147zlo79d",
    "Conference Presentations & Participations\nPresented at the “19th Biennial International Conference on Media & Communication, MENTION”. Malaysia. October 28-30, 2025.\nPresented at the “4th Annual Global Forum” (Online). April 23, 2025.\nAttended and presented at the “MEDCOM.” April 8-9, 2025.\nAttended and presented at the “MetropolisKL,” Malaysia. November 14-17, 2024.\nAttended & Presented at the “18th Biennial International Conference on Media & Communication, MENTION.” Malaysia. November 14-16, 2023.\nPresented at “The First Asian Academic Summit 2022,” Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia, Malaysia. November 7, 2022.\nPresented at the “POGRES2021,” Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia, Malaysia. December 15, 2021.\nPresented at the “Media in America” (online). March 25, 2021.\nPresented at the “20th International Conference on Social Sciences,” Zurich University of Arts, Switzerland. September 6-7\nth\n, 2019.\nPresented at ‘Language and Literature Teaching: Exploring Opportunities and Facing the Challenges,’ Stamford University, Bangladesh. January 27, 2011.\nParticipated in “The 10th International Language, Literature and Stylistic Symposium,” Ankara, Turkey.  November 3-5, 2010.",
    "Workshop\nWorked as Rapporteur at the “2nd AICHR CONSULTATION ON THE RIGHT TO DEVELOPMENT TO ENHANCE THE ASEAN COMMUNITY Program”. April 28-29, 2025.\n“Workshop for experts on migration.” Institute of Malaysian and International Studies, UKM. November 7-9, 2024.\n“Seminar on Migration and Refugees,” Institute of Malaysian and International Studies, UKM, Malaysia. August 29, 2024.\n‘The International Media in America, America in Media Doctoral Workshop.’. March 22, 2021.\n“Professional Skills Development Program (PSDP), BRAC University. 2007."
